### 🧪 **Ultra-Granular TVOC Thresholds and Descriptions**

| **Level** | **TVOC Range (ppb)** | **Approx. µg/m³** | **Air Quality Description** |
|-----------|----------------------|-------------------|------------------------------|
| A1        | 0 – 25               | 0 – ~0.12         | Ultra-pristine air; typical of filtered cleanrooms or outdoor rural settings |
| A2        | 26 – 50              | ~0.13 – ~0.24     | Exceptionally clean; ideal for sensitive environments (e.g. healthcare, labs) |
| A3        | 51 – 75              | ~0.25 – ~0.37     | Very low VOC presence; no odour or irritation risk |
| B1        | 76 – 100             | ~0.38 – ~0.49     | Excellent indoor air; optimal for all occupants |
| B2        | 101 – 125            | ~0.50 – ~0.61     | Very good; minimal VOCs, no health concerns |
| B3        | 126 – 150            | ~0.62 – ~0.73     | Good air quality; suitable for long-term exposure |
| C1        | 151 – 175            | ~0.74 – ~0.85     | Acceptable; low-level VOCs may be detectable by sensitive individuals |
| C2        | 176 – 200            | ~0.86 – ~0.98     | Slightly elevated; odour possible, no health risk |
| C3        | 201 – 225            | ~0.99 – ~1.10     | Fair; mild discomfort possible in enclosed spaces |
| D1        | 226 – 250            | ~1.11 – ~1.22     | Borderline moderate; ventilation may be beneficial |
| D2        | 251 – 275            | ~1.23 – ~1.34     | Moderate; symptoms possible in sensitive groups |
| D3        | 276 – 300            | ~1.35 – ~1.47     | Upper limit of “Good”; approaching warning zone |
| E1        | 301 – 400            | ~1.48 – ~1.96     | Warning zone; odours and irritation may occur |
| E2        | 401 – 500            | ~1.97 – ~2.45     | Elevated VOCs; ventilation recommended |
| E3        | 501 – 600            | ~2.46 – ~2.94     | Moderate pollution; complaints likely |
| F1        | 601 – 750            | ~2.95 – ~3.68     | Poor air quality; symptoms expected |
| F2        | 751 – 1000           | ~3.69 – ~4.90     | Alert level; unsafe for prolonged exposure |
| G1        | 1001 – 1500          | ~4.91 – ~7.35     | High VOCs; urgent action required |
| G2        | 1501 – 2000          | ~7.36 – ~9.80     | Very poor; acute symptoms likely |
| G3        | 2001 – 3000          | ~9.81 – ~14.70    | Hazardous; evacuation or ventilation essential |
| H1        | > 3000               | > ~14.70          | Severe pollution; toxic exposure risk |

