### 🍷 **Ultra-Granular Ethanol Index Thresholds and Descriptions**

| **Level** | **Ethanol Index Value** | **Description** |
|-----------|--------------------------|-----------------|
| A1        | 0.00 – 0.05              | Baseline; no ethanol detected |
| A2        | 0.06 – 0.10              | Trace ethanol; typical of unoccupied spaces |
| B1        | 0.11 – 0.15              | Very low ethanol; may result from human respiration |
| B2        | 0.16 – 0.20              | Low ethanol; background from mild product use |
| C1        | 0.21 – 0.25              | Light ethanol presence; no health concern |
| C2        | 0.26 – 0.30              | Slightly elevated; odour may be perceptible |
| D1        | 0.31 – 0.35              | Moderate ethanol; ventilation may be beneficial |
| D2        | 0.36 – 0.40              | Noticeable ethanol; may cause mild irritation |
| E1        | 0.41 – 0.45              | Elevated ethanol; approaching alert threshold |
| E2        | 0.46 – 0.50              | High ethanol; alert may trigger depending on context |
| F1        | 0.51 – 0.60              | Alert zone; strong ethanol presence from sprays or solvents |
| F2        | 0.61 – 0.70              | High ethanol; discomfort likely in enclosed spaces |
| G1        | 0.71 – 0.80              | Very high ethanol; ventilation strongly advised |
| G2        | 0.81 – 0.90              | Severe ethanol spike; possible spill or misuse |
| H1        | 0.91 – 1.00              | Dangerous ethanol level; flammability or toxicity risk |
| H2        | > 1.00                   | Excessive ethanol; immediate action required |

